This paper deals with image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel architecture for the network, which involves combining local and global features, and using Inception modules (cs.LG). The paper also discusses domain adaptation, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves image retrieval, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
